  <brief_title>The Effect of Lifestyle-Adjustments Prior to Medical Treatment on the Effect of Medical Treatment in Reflux Patients</brief_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>AstraZeneca</agency>
      <agency_class>Industry</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>AstraZeneca</source>
  <oversight_info>
    <has_dmc>No</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to determine whether the improvement in the quality of life
      after an initial treatment with esomeprazole 40mg for reflux disease is the same in patients
      who have already made lifestyle-adjustments as in patients who have not implemented
      lifestyle-adjustments prior to the start of treatment (baseline)
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
